  "DrikPanchang refuses |lat| above ~62 ('High Latitudes are not entertained', Tromso geoname 3133895); this engine computes Whole Sign charts there and returns placidus_cusps=None.",
  "begins times are local wall clock; hours >= 24 mean the next civil day. Coordinates are geonames values for the geoname-id, cross-checked via sunrise agreement < 30s.",
  "1943 Kolkata table is in India's war-time DST clock (UTC+06:30, tzdb Asia/Kolkata) — verified: interpreting it at +05:30 misses every window by ~1h."
